  "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EThe neck is a complex region of anatomy and can offer unique challenges clinically. \u0026nbsp; Housing portions of the brain stem and spinal cord, being a sharp diagnostician is paramount.\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp; Once arriving at the working diagnosis, crafting a clinical approach to yield the best results is made easier with addition of PBM to your care plan.\u0026nbsp; From trigger points to DDD and DJD, we will explore most of the more common neck complaints and conditions and discuss some additional unique conditions as well. \u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EBoth acute and chronic neck pain will be addressed, along with some guidelines to blend PBM with common daily strategies patients are already using to yield a faster recovery.\u0026nbsp; Beyond pain, PBM is integral to completing the patient\u0026rsquo;s full recovery.\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp; Join Dr. Chris Carraway for the October webinar as he presents an in-depth review of photobiomodulation techniques for managing neck pain.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cbr /\u003E"
}]]></Value>
